.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-RESET 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-reset \- remove claims from a batch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch reset
\fB\-\-from\fR \fIBATCH\fR
[\fB\-\-to\fR \fIDEST_BATCH\fR]
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR [\fIPATH\fR] | \fB\-\-files\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B reset
removes the batch's record that selected lines belong to that batch, without
changing the index or working tree. With
.B \-\-to
the removed claims are moved into another batch first.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-from " BATCH
Remove claims from
.IR BATCH .
.TP
.BI "\-\-to " DEST_BATCH
Move removed claims into
.I DEST_BATCH
before removing them from the source batch.
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Reset specific displayed line IDs from one file.
.TP
.B \-\-file
.RI [ PATH ]
Reset one file from the batch.
.TP
.BI "\-\-files " PATTERN "..."
Reset all batch files matched by gitignore-style patterns.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-sift (1)
